{{Quote|While it is true that a Jedi uses his power only for defense, never for attack, it is equally true that a Jedi must nevertheless prepare with great vigilance, for only the Force knows when you may face your greatest battle.|Excerpt from Jedi Master Vo'ren Faalo's ''Book of Practical Lightsaber Technique''|<ref name="Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim">''[[Galaxy Guide 9: Fragments from the Rim]]''</ref>}}
The '''Book of Practical Lightsaber Technique''' was a book written by [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Vo'ren Faalo/Legends|Vo'ren Faalo]] that described his own formal [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] training that he developed for his young [[Padawan/Legends|apprentices]]. The book contained at least seven volumes. In his book, Faalo detailed a [[Faalo's cadences|series of cadences]] in which a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] attempted to manipulate small steel bearings atop candles with their lightsabers, as well as a telekinetic technique, which would be later called [[Faalo's Will]].<ref name="Card-SWGTCG-Faalo's Will">{{SWGTCG|set=Galactic Hunters|cardname=Faalo's Will}}</ref> Some masters were known to have used his practice techniques as part of training their own students. One such person was [[Adalric Cessius Brandl]] who used Faalo's practice techniques to teach [[Fable Astin/Legends|Fable Astin]].

